GigShield – Parametric Income Protection for Gig Workers
Overview

GigShield is a parametric insurance platform designed to protect the income of gig economy workers such as delivery partners. The system automatically monitors environmental and social disruptions (e.g., heavy rain, extreme heat, pollution, strikes) and triggers insurance payouts when predefined thresholds are crossed.

The platform eliminates manual claim filing by using automated triggers and real-time validation, ensuring fast payouts and fraud prevention.

Problem Statement

Gig workers often experience income loss due to disruptions such as:

Heavy rainfall

Extreme heat conditions

Air pollution

Flood alerts

Local transport or market strikes

Traditional insurance processes are slow and require manual claims. GigShield solves this by using parametric insurance triggers that automatically initiate payouts when disruption thresholds are reached.

